cted to mise-tasks/\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\", start_line, lines\\\\n        }\\\\n    } else {\\\\n        lines++\\\\n```\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"thread_id\\\": 2862132161,\\n    \\\"path\\\": \\\"mise-tasks/lint/mise\\\",\\n    \\\"line\\\": 9,\\n    \\\"comments\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"toothbrush\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\": \\\"Sorry i got nerd sniped, haha.  We could make a ±one-liner:\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```sh\\\\r\\\\nmultiline_run_blocks=$(dasel -i toml 'len(..run.filter($this =~ r/\\\\\\\\n/))' < mise.toml)\\\\r\\\\n[[ $multiline_run_blocks -eq 0 ]] || (echo \\\\\\\"mise.toml: multi-line script should be extracted to mise-tasks\\\\\\\"; exit 1)\\\\r\\\\n```\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n😅 \\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"toothbrush\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\": \\\"This uses [dasel](https://daseldocs.tomwright.me/) which is a bit like `jq` for TOML.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"khaong\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\": \\\"I think we can live with the awk here rather than bringing in dasel...(famous last words) - but we can always replace this later\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"thread_id\\\": 2862136280,\\n    \\\"path\\\": \\\"mise-tasks/test/e2e/claude\\\",\\n    \\\"line\\\": 15,\\n    \\\"comments\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"toothbrush\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\": \\\"This file is almost identical to `mise-tasks/test/e2e/gemini` and `mise-tasks/test/e2e/opencode`.  How about having one `mise-tasks/test/e2e` script which we can run with:\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n```sh\\\\r\\\\nE2E_AGENT=claude-code mise run test:e2e\\\\r\\\\nE2E_AGENT=gemini-cli mise run test:e2e\\\\r\\\\n# ...etc\\\\r\\\\n```\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"author\\\": \\\"khaong\\\",\\n        \\\"body\\\": \\\"refactored to use --agent instead of having specific mise tasks - this lets us leave the mise tooling untouched when extending to new agents\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  {\\